Many Basques arrived in Chile in the 16th,17th,18th,19th and early 20th century from their homeland in northern [[Spain]] (see [[Basque Country (historical territory)|Basque Provinces]]) and parts of southwestern [[France]], as [[conquistadors]], [[soldiers]], [[sailors]], [[merchants]], [[priests]] and [[labourers]]. Due to their traditional hard work and entrepreneurship, many of them rose to the top of the social scale and intermarried into the Chilean elites formed by [[Basque people|Basque]]s, giving birth to the new Basque-Chilean aristocracy in Chile. This union is the basis of the Chilean elite of today. But also, they immensely contributed to the ethnic make up of the bulk of the [[Chilean people|Chilean population]].
Many years after the first waves of settlers, thousands of Basque refugees fleeing [[Spanish Civil War]] in 1939 also settled and have many descendants in the country and have even intermarried with Spanish ethnic groups other than Castilians, and other [[European ethnic groups]]. An estimated 1.6 million (10%) and 3.2 million (20%) Chileans have a surname (one or both) of Basque origin.<ref name="Diariovasco">[http://www.diariovasco.com/pg060724/prensa/noticias/AlDia/200607/24/DVA-ALD-003.html Diariovasco.]</ref><ref name="deia.com">[http://www.deia.com/es/impresa/2008/05/22/bizkaia/ekonomia/469496.php entrevista al Presidente de la C<U+00E1>mara vasca.]</ref><ref>[http://www.osasun.ejgv.euskadi.net/r52-20726/es/contenidos/noticia/albis12_257_txile_08_11/es_txile/albis12_257_txile_08_11.html vascos] '''Ainara Madariaga''': Autora del estudio ''"Imaginarios vascos desde Chile La construcci<U+00F3>n de imaginarios vascos en Chile durante el siglo XX"''.</ref><ref>[http://www.euskonews.com/0072zbk/gaia7204es.html Basques au Chili.]</ref><ref>'''''Contacto Interling<U+00FC><U+00ED>stico e intercultural en el mundo hispano.instituto valenciano de lenguas y culturas. Universitat de Val<U+00E8>ncia Cita:''''' " Un 20% de la poblaci<U+00F3>n chilena tiene su origen en el Pa<U+00ED>s Vasco"''.</ref><ref>{{es icon}} [http://www.empresariosvascos.cl/boletines/2008-11-03-BOLETIN-EMPREBASK.pdf La poblaci<U+00F3>n chilena con ascendencia vasca bordea entre el 15% y el 20% del total, por lo que es uno de los pa<U+00ED>ses con mayor presencia de emigrantes venidos de Euskadi.]</ref><ref>[http://www.euzkoetxeachile.cl/libros/04-De%20los%20Vascos%20Onati%20y%20los%20Elorza-2.pdf] '''DE LOS VASCOS, O<U+00D1>ATI Y LOS ELORZA''' ''Waldo Ayarza Elorza''.</ref><ref>{{es icon}}  [http://www.euskalkultura.com/noticias/jon-erdozia-nuevo-delegado-en-chile-iniciativas-vasco-chilenas-como-emprebask-son-exportables-a-otros-paises?language_sync=1 Presencia vasca en Chile.]</ref>

To describe the Basque-Chilean relationship, we cite [[Miguel de Unamuno]], who said: "There are at least two things that clearly can be attributed to the Basques: the [[Society of Jesus]] and the [[Republic of Chile]]."<ref>"<U+00AB>La Compa<U+00F1><U+00ED>a de Jes<U+00FA>s y la Rep<U+00FA>blica de Chile son las dos grandes haza<U+00F1>as del pueblo vascongado<U+00BB>, sol<U+00ED>a decir don Miguel de Unamuno". Miguel de Unamuno used to say "The Company of Jesus and the Republic of Chile are the two great achievements of the Basque people." [http://www.filosofia.org/hem/194/alf/ez2302a.htm]</ref>

== History ==
The Basque presence in [[Chile]] began in the [[conquista]] period, 
for in the armies of the first colonizers came a contingent important soldiers from the [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque Provinces]] and from [[Navarra]]. In the 16th century, of the 157 Peninsular families that settled in Chile, 39 had Basque [[surnames]]. This number progressively grew, as reflected in the number of governors of Basque origin.

Forms a regional [[immigration]] corridor between [[Spain]] and Chile, one that is large, visible, and continues over time. [[Basque diaspora|Basque immigration]] can be divided into historical periods: [[Discovery (observation)|discovery]], foundation, and [[Viceroyalty of Peru|colonial period]]; the wave of immigration of the 18th century; and the recent immigrants (19th and 20th centuries). 

During the 18th century, the country experimented a mass immigration coming from the Basque provinces and [[Navarra]], by the end of the 18th century represents 20% of [[Demographics of Chile|the Chilean population]].{{Notinsource|date=April 2014}}<ref>[http://www.osasun.ejgv.euskadi.net/r52-20726/es/contenidos/noticia/albis12_257_txile_08_11/es_txile/albis12_257_txile_08_11.html Vascos en Chile.]</ref> This raised the Basques to being the most important regional group in the population, displacing the natives and descendants of those born in [[New Castile]], [[Old Castile]], and [[Andaluc<U+00ED>a]]. These immigrant families initially dedicated themselves to their preferred form of business, and in successive years produced many alliances with families of Castilian origin possessing lands and titles, giving birth to a new social group known in Chilean history as the "''Castilian-Basque Aristocracy."''

In the second half of the 19th century came a new wave of [[Basque people|Basque immigration]], this time as much from the Spanish regions as the [[France|French]]. This migratory flood are extended until the end of the [[Spanish Civil War]].

==Notable Basque-Chileans==
* [[Pedro Aguirre Cerda]],<ref>[http://cvc.cervantes.es/el_rinconete/anteriores/julio_09/08672707_01.asp Pedro Aguirre Cerda.]</ref> President of Chile (1938<U+2013>1941)
* [[Isabel Allende]],<ref>[http://www.metroactive.com/papers/metro/06.25.98/allende-9825.html Isabel Allende]</ref> writer
* [[Salvador Allende]],<ref>[http://masones.wordpress.com/2009/06/28/el-personaje-masonico-de-junio-salvador-allende-gossens/ Salvador Allende.]</ref> President of Chile (1970<U+2013>1973)
* [[Maricarmen Arrigorriaga]],<ref>[http://actrizchilena.blogspot.com/2008/02/algo-ms-sobre-maricarmen-arrigorriaga.html Maricarmen Arrigorriaga.]</ref> actress
* [[Jos<U+00E9> Manuel Balmaceda]],<ref>[http://html.rincondelvago.com/historia-de-chile_6.html Jos<U+00E9> Manuel Balmaceda.]</ref> President of Chile (1886<U+2013>1891)
* [[Manuel Baquedano]], <ref>[http://www.genealog.cl/Chile/B/Baquedano.]</ref> Commander-in-chief of the  Chilean Army during the War of the Pacific
* Juan Guzman Cruchaga (1895<U+2013>1979) was a Chilean poet and diplomat. He won the Chilean National Prize for Literature in 1962
* [[Alberto Blest Gana]],<ref>[http://cvc.cervantes.es/el_rinconete/anteriores/julio_07/04072007_01.asp Alberto Blest Gana.]</ref> writer and diplomat
* [[Felipe Camiroaga]],<ref>[http://www.segunda.cl/modulos/generacion/mobileASP/detailNew.asp?idNoticia=CM816L0HF20090430&strNamePage=LUCSGTL54SG3004.jpg&codCuerpo=701&iNumPag=54&strFecha=2009-04-30&iPage=1&tipoPantalla=240 Felipe Camiroaga.]</ref> actor and TV host
* [[Javiera Carrera]],<ref>[http://diario.elmercurio.cl/detalle/index.asp?id={09b31ebd-bb5c-419c-87c7-3069540a13e3} Javiera Carrera]</ref> patriot
* [[Jos<U+00E9> Miguel Carrera]],<ref>[http://diario.elmercurio.cl/detalle/index.asp?id={09b31ebd-bb5c-419c-87c7-3069540a13e3} Jos<U+00E9> Miguel Carrera]</ref> Army general, President of the Government Junta and hero of the War of Chilean Independence
* [[Federico Err<U+00E1>zuriz Za<U+00F1>artu]],<ref>[http://www.escritores.cl/base.php?f1=articulos/texto/Penamunoz.htm Federico Err<U+00E1>zuriz Za<U+00F1>artu.]</ref> President of Chile (1871<U+2013>1876)
* [[Domingo Eyzaguirre]],<ref>[http://www.sanbernardo.cl/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=3&Itemid=18 Domingo Eyzaguirre.]</ref> politician
* [[Alejandro Gorostiaga]],<ref>[http://www.diarioeldia.cl/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1827&Itemid=177 Alejandro Gorostiaga.]</ref> Army officer
* [[Luc<U+00ED>a Hiriart]],<ref>[http://www.voltairenet.org/article120115.html Luc<U+00ED>a Hiriart.]</ref> former First Lady of Chile (1973<U+2013>1990)
* [[Alberto Hurtado|Alberto Hurtado Cruchaga]],<ref>[http://sid.usal.es/mostrarficha.aspx?id=17668&fichero=1.1 Alberto Hurtado Cruchaga.]</ref> Jesuit priest and saint
* [[Marta Larraechea]],<ref>[http://democratascristianosantofagasta.blogspot.com/2009/05/el-peso-de-martita-en-la-campana-de.html Marta Larraechea.]</ref> former First Lady of Chile (1994<U+2013>2000)
* [[Alberto Larraguibel]],<ref>[http://www.euskalkultura.com/noticias/recordando-la-hazana-del-capitan-larraguibel?language_sync=1 Alberto Larraguibel.]</ref> Army officer and equestrian
* [[Fernando Larra<U+00ED>n]],<ref>[http://www.chileazul.cl/foro/index.php?topic=27022.0;wap2 Fernando Larra<U+00ED>n.]</ref> actor
* [[Hern<U+00E1>n Larra<U+00ED>n]],<ref>[http://www.chileazul.cl/foro/index.php?topic=27022.0;wap2 Hern<U+00E1>n Larra<U+00ED>n.]</ref> politician
* [[Mar<U+00ED>a Eugenia Larra<U+00ED>n]],<ref>[http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/antialone.html?page=http://www.lanacion.cl/p4_lanacion/site/artic/20040131/pags/20040131185807.html Mar<U+00ED>a Eugenia "Kenita" Larra<U+00ED>n.]</ref> model
* [[Roberto Matta|Roberto Matta Echaurren]],<ref>[http://www2.udec.cl/~mariasmo/pintores/Roberto%20Matta.htm Roberto Matta Echaurren.]</ref> painter
* [[Pablo Neruda]],<ref name="ReferenceA">''Possible Paradises'', Basque Emigration to Latin America By ''Jos<U+00E9> Manuel Azcona Pastor.''</ref> poet and Nobel laureate
* [[Bernardo O'Higgins]],<ref>[http://www.scielo.cl/pdf/historia/v36/art01.pdf Bernardo O'Higgins.]</ref> Army general, Supreme Director and hero of the War of Chilean Independence
* [[Augusto Pinochet|Augusto Pinochet Ugarte]],<ref>[http://lahoradelpueblo.blogspot.com/2006/12/augusto-pinochet-el-insulso-hijo-del.html Augusto Pinochet Ugarte].</ref> Army General and military dictator (1973<U+2013>1990)
* [[Sebasti<U+00E1>n Pi<U+00F1>era|Sebasti<U+00E1>n Pi<U+00F1>era Echenique]],<ref>[http://pinera2010.cl/2009/12/14/chile-necesita-un-verdadero-renacimiento/] Sebasti<U+00E1>n Pi<U+00F1>era Echenique</ref> President of Chile (2010<U+2013>2014)
* [[Manuel Rodr<U+00ED>guez Erdoiza]],<ref>[http://www.educomputacion.cl/index2.php?option=com_content&do_pdf=1&id=369 Manuel Rodr<U+00ED>guez Erdoiza.]</ref> guerrilla fighter and hero of the War of Chilean Independence
* [[Fernando Solabarrieta]],<ref>[http://www.puntomujer.emol.com/solteras/noticia/detallenoticia.asp?id=%7B780BF766-B372-4C54-815B-03026F7F7C5A%7D%3C Fernando Solabarrieta.]</ref> journalist and sports commentator
* [[Benjam<U+00ED>n Vicu<U+00F1>a Mackenna]],<ref>[http://www.chileazul.cl/index.php?=77892.0;wap2 Benjam<U+00ED>n Vicu<U+00F1>a Mackenna.]</ref> politician, historian and writer
* [[Paz Yrarr<U+00E1>zaval]],<ref>[http://www.genealog.cl/Chile/I.html Genealog<U+00ED>a de familias Chilenas; Irarr<U+00E1>zaval, Yrarr<U+00E1>zabal, Irarr<U+00E1>zabal]</ref> actress
* [[Adolfo Zald<U+00ED>var]],<ref>[http://www.diariocritico.com/2008/Junio/opinion/anasagasti/81843/anasagasti.html Adolfo Zald<U+00ED>var.]</ref> politician
* [[Andr<U+00E9>s Zald<U+00ED>var]],<ref>[http://www.diariocritico.com/2008/Junio/opinion/anasagasti/81843/anasagasti.html Andr<U+00E9>s Zald<U+00ED>var.]</ref> politician
* [[An<U+00ED>bal Za<U+00F1>artu]],<ref>[http://www.genealog.cl/Chile/Z.html An<U+00ED>bal Za<U+00F1>artu.]</ref> politician

